subject: Adapt packaging/cups.spec for 1.6.4
commitMessage:
Adapt packaging/cups.spec for 1.6.4

- Do not fail if the fonts directory does not exist.

- Use macro to run configure.

- Disable xinetd support.

- Stop fiddling with locales.

- Disable systemd support (until the patch for the code is ported).

- Files removed upstream
  - filters (STR #3930): bannertops, commandtoescpx, commandtopclx,
    imagetops, imagetoraster, pdftops, rastertoescpx, rastertopclx,
    texttops,
  - backends: serial, parallel,
  - libraries: libcupsdriver,
  - programmes: cups-polld.

- Files added upstream: cups-files.conf, cups-files.conf.5.gz
  cups-snmp.5.gz.

Change-Id: I7fb71a76accf6b6713e84e79710a7687a18df3c4
Signed-off-by: Łukasz Stelmach <l.stelmach@samsung.com>

subject: Only use systemd socket activation, do not enable service itself
commitMessage: Only use systemd socket activation, do not enable service itself

comments.message: Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1
Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

Patch Set 1:

More of a documentary comment here for myself:
Enabling a .service file in systemd makes the service
start during the boot sequence
For socket activated services we should only enable the .socket, and .path if present.
systemd will listen on that socket and spawn the service
when a connection is made, i.e. when GNOME probes for printers as and when the desktop is started.
This is part of the move to get secondary services out of the initial boot sequence.
Patch Set 1: Verified+1 Code-Review+2
Change has been successfully merged into the git repository.
